President Trump welcomed young athletes to the White House for a special White House Sports and Fitness Day. He thanked Secretary Azar and Assistant Secretary Giroir for their work, as well as Ivanka for her leadership in refocusing the Council. The President announced the members of the President's Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition, which will be co-chaired by Mariano Rivera, Herschel Walker, and Misty May-Treanor. President Trump emphasized the importance of sports in teaching valuable life lessons and building character. He expressed concern over the declining youth participation in sports and directed the council to develop a national strategy to increase participation. The President then kicked off a White House Field Day, which featured various sports activities.